Text.Value: Fair warning - the guildmaster wants no fraternising with the Zhentarim. They're here to work, not to share war stories.
*The names ring familiar: two of the many crews that make up the Guild, a loose collective with ties to every criminal enterprise in the city's underworld.*
If you need any ideas on how this place should run, just look to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Eager, wants to ingratiate himself with us

Text.Value: Neither. I run a crew called the Wormskulls.
So do we just... sign up? Get Zhentarim kit of our own?

EditorData.NodeContext: Nonplussed, uncertain what to do next.

Text.Value: Leave.
The latest challenger to the Guild's position. But probably the first one to actually make us sweat.
I know something of the Stone Lord. You'll want your Zhentarim at their best.
He came out of nowhere and ate up half our turf in a tenday. So if you're speaking to the guildmaster, maybe step soft around the topic, hm?
Nine-Fingers was the only thing keeping the kingpins united. I doubt the Zhentarim can do the same, no matter how pretty their uniforms are.

EditorData.NodeContext: Doubt for the future - just because the Zhent are in control doesn't mean things are better.

Text.Value: The Stone Lord? Who's that?
Nice to see a little ambition amongst the smaller crews. I can't help you, but look around for a halfling named Tut.
That chair's yours for the taking. Better than leaving it absent for these clowns to fight over.

EditorData.NodeContext: Eager, wants to ingratiate himself with us

Text.Value: Nine-Fingers is planning to take the Stone Lord down first. I need to know where.
I'm sure you call yourselves that - but there's no crew paying tribute under that name. And you don't want to owe the Guild money.
Didn't think the Zhentarim would turn on us so easily. Inatra seemed... honest, gods help me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Nonplussed, know he sounds naive to have trusted a merc.

Text.Value: You won't. The Black Network is working for us. The Guild is hardly a soft target, but we're not set up for the turf war the Stone Lord's set on fighting.
Nine-Fingers has been known to pour her secrets in his ear, time to time. Maybe 'cos he rinses them out with wine.
You rid us of our Stone Lord problem. Just a pity you didn't settle a payday with Nine-Fingers first, eh?

EditorData.NodeContext: Making a weak joke about our success - a little intimidated by us

Text.Value: Remember - no distracting the Zhent. We want them sharp if the Stone Lord comes calling.
They won't be much use to us if they're drinking and dicing when the Stone Lord kicks the door down.
Well whoever he is, he doesn't seem very keen on talking.
I didn't think I'd ever see the Guild and the Zhentarim working together.
I'm not with any crew. Why?
In between scores, then? There's no shame in that. This Stone Lord business has even the bigger crews shutting up shop for a while.
Up the stairs. She keeps an open door - to those who don't waste her time, anyway.
'Child of Hoar'? Is that an insult?
Consider me an independent operator.
I'd like to speak to the guildmaster.
You're one of the few alive who know anything about him, then.
You're so sure the Stone Lord is going to attack?
Looking to prove yourself, are you? Carve your name in the guildmaster's good books?
It's a gang. Pious thugs worshipping the god of petty justice. If you'd met them, you'd probably have a brand on your head - so, steer clear.
Can't say I've heard of you. Spare me the story behind the name - I'm sure it's very scary.
Right, which crew are you with? Bell-Breakers? The Children of Hoar?
Leave.

EditorData.logicalname: BASE STATE - DIDN'T ASK ABOUT AMBUSH
